snippet.textDisplay:
Lyrics of the song:

Syama rai kalia
(oh! Lord Krishna)

ohe bi nandiya – 2
borang saraaaaaii...
Kunbone saarila dhenu he hari
kadam tale kana muruuuli bajai -2
(Under the shade of kadam tree,
with all his cattle,
 kanha plays the flute)

{Jamunar balite, syama rai kalia
kisna banhi bajai
ohe bi nandiya } -2
mathare mukuli suli he hari
kadam tale kana muruuuli bajai -2
(along the banks of Yamuna river,
lord krishna is playing the flute
mother Yashoda has heard him now)

O syam kalia, kot aji palabi
toye syam kalia, kot aji palabi
jamunar balite, kadambar talate -2
merai merai bandhiba
tuke syam kalia, kot aji palabi
toye syam kalia, kot aji palabi
(O lord krishna,
where will you run today?
to Yamuna riverside?
to the shade of kadam tree?
Mother Yashoda will catch you,
and will tie you to a tree.)

{brindabanur maje kanhu, oh syam kalia
go dhenu sarai prabhu, o syam kalia} -2
Ooo....
bankhi rawe gopi manak bhulai he
o syam kalia, kot aji palabi
jamunar balite, kadambar talate
merai merai bandhibo
tuke syam kalia, kot aji palabi
toye(o) syam kalia, kot aji palabi -7
(In the fields of vrindavan,
krishna's cows are grazing,
while he is enjoying playing his flute.
On hearing the sound of his flute,
gopis lose all their senses and get immersed into the music.)

snippet.textDisplay: This song transports one to the valleys of Assam! The soul of the land, its celebrations...spring season, love and romance in the air...the full flavor of youth, and its playfulness... only a short season in one's whole life! Happy, but a touch of sadness lurking behind it with a sense of loss...precious! Highlight moments; 0:21 The starting humming itself is pretty romantic & sexy. 1:25 lead guitar sings! What controlled playing! Perfect amount of time, not too much or less, 1:45, that husky voice again, pretty seductive! 2:57 picks up the pace...4:00 Papon & Sugandha are jamming! They have good chemistry, 4:09 look at her cute grin! That last part with Papon's humming over transports one into the expansive landscape of the valleys! That traditional dancer with symbols also adds color to the visual. Pure Bliss!
